* `tick_upper` - Upper tick of the range\0a\0a# Returns\0a* `Ok(())` if ticks are valid\0a* `Err` if ticks are invalid (wrong order, out of bounds, or misaligned with tick_spacing)\00\00\00\00\00\0bcheck_ticks\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0atick_lower\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0atick_upper\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\01\00\00\03\e9\00\00\03\ed\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00}Returns the current ledger timestamp.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aCurrent timestamp in seconds\00\00\00\00\00\00\0fblock_timestamp\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\06\00\00\00\00\00\00\01:Initializes the pool with a starting price.\0a\0aMust be called before any liquidity operations. Can only be called once.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a* `sqrt_price_x96` - Initial sqrt price in Q64.96 format\0a\0a# Returns\0a* `Ok(())` on success\0a* `Err(AlreadyInitialized)` if pool is already initialized\00\00\00\00\00\0ainitialize\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0esqrt_price_x96\00\00\00\00\00\0c\00\00\00\01\00\00\03\e9\00\00\03\ed\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\02dSwaps tokens in the pool.\0a\0aTransfers tokens from sender and sends output tokens to recipient.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a* `sender` - Address providing input tokens (requires auth)\0a* `recipient` - Address receiving output tokens\0a* `zero_for_one` - True if swapping token0 for token1, false otherwise\0a* `amount_specified` - Amount to swap (positive for exact input, negative for exact output)\0a* `sqrt_price_limit_x96` - Price limit for the swap in Q64.96 format\0a\0a# Returns\0a* `Ok(SwapResult)` containing amounts swapped and final price\0a* `Err` if swap fails (locked, invalid price limit, etc.)\00\00\00\04swap\00\00\00\06\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06sender\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\09recipient\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0czero_for_one\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10amount_specified\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\14sqrt_price_limit_x96\00\00\00\0c\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05hints\00\00\00\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0bOracleHints\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\03\e9\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0aSwapResult\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\03VSwaps tokens using prefunded input already held by the pool.\0a\0aAssumes input tokens have been transferred to the pool before calling.\0aOnly authorized routers can call this function. Verifies available delta\0avia baseline accounting system before executing the swap.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a* `router` - Address of the authorized router (requires auth)\0a* `recipient` - Address receiving output tokens\0a* `zero_for_one` - True if swapping token0 for token1, false otherwise\0a* `amount_specified` - Amount to swap (positive for exact input, negative for exact output)\0a* `sqrt_price_limit_x96` - Price limit for the swap in Q64.96 format\0a\0a# Returns\0a* `Ok(SwapResult)` containing amounts swapped and final price\0a* `Err(Unauthorized)` if router is not authorized\0a* `Err` on other failures (locked, invalid price limit, insufficient balance)\00\00\00\00\00\0eswap_prefunded\00\00\00\00\00\06\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06router\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\09recipient\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0czero_for_one\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10amount_specified\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\14sqrt_price_limit_x96\00\00\00\0c\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05hints\00\00\00\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0bOracleHints\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\03\e9\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0aSwapResult\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\caManages authorization for routers allowed to call `swap_prefunded`.\0a\0aOnly the pool's factory can call this function.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a* `factory` - Address of the factory (requires auth, must match pool's factory)\0a* `router` - Address of the router to authorize/unauthorize\0a* `allowed` - True to authorize, false to remove authorization\0a\0a# Returns\0a* `Ok(())` on success\0a* `Err(Unauthorized)` if caller is not the pool's factory\00\00\00\00\00\15set_router_authorized\00\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\07factory\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06router\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\07allowed\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\01\00\00\03\e9\00\00\03\ed\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\02jBurns liquidity from a position.\0a\0aRemoves liquidity from the specified tick range and credits the owed\0atokens to the position. Tokens must be collected separately via `collect`.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a* `owner` - Address owning the position (requires auth)\0a* `tick_lower` - Lower tick of the position range\0a* `tick_upper` - Upper tick of the position range\0a* `amount` - Amount of liquidity to burn\0a\0a# Returns\0a* `Ok((amount0, amount1))` - Amounts of token0 and token1 owed to the position\0a* `Err(Locked)` if pool is currently locked\0a* `Err` on other failures (invalid ticks, position not found)\00\00\00\00\00\04burn\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05owner\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0atick_lower\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0atick_upper\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06amount\00\00\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05hints\00\00\00\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0bOracleHints\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\03\e9\00\00\03\ed\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\9bCollects fees accumulated by a liquidity position.\0a\0aTransfers owed tokens to the recipient. Fees are computed when liquidity\0ais added or removed via mint/burn, not when collecting.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a* `recipient` - Address receiving the fees (requires auth, must be position owner)\0a* `tick_lower` - Lower tick of the position range\0a* `tick_upper` - Upper tick of the position range\0a* `amount0_requested` - Maximum amount of token0 to collect\0a* `amount1_requested` - Maximum amount of token1 to collect\0a\0a# Returns\0a* `Ok((amount0, amount1))` - Actual amounts collected (min of requested vs owed)\0a* `Err(Error)` if position fee update fails\00\00\00\00\07collect\00\00\00\00\06\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05owner\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\09recipient\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0atick_lower\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0atick_upper\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\11amount0_requested\00\00\00\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\11amount1_requested\00\00\00\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\01\00\00\03\e9\00\00\03\ed\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\1fCollects protocol fees accumulated by the pool.\0a\0aOnly the factory owner can call this function. Keeps a minimum of 1 token\0ain the slot to save on storage gas costs.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a* `recipient` - Address receiving the protocol fees (requires factory owner auth)\0a* `amount0_requested` - Maximum amount of token0 to collect\0a* `amount1_requested` - Maximum amount of token1 to collect\0a\0a# Returns\0a* `Ok((amount0, amount1))` - Actual amounts collected\0a* `Err(Error)` if pool is not initialized or params are missing\00\00\00\00\10collect_protocol\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\09recipient\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\11amount0_requested\00\00\00\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\11amount1_requested\00\00\00\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\01\00\00\03\e9\00\00\03\ed\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\bfBegin a flash loan\0a\0aOnly the authorized FlashExecutor can call this.\0aMust be followed by flash_end() in the same transaction.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `recipient` - Address to receive borrowed tokens\0a* `amount0` - Amount of token0 to borrow\0a* `amount1` - Amount of token1 to borrow\0a* `initiator` - Address of the flash loan initiator (must be FlashExecutor)\0a\0a# Returns\0a* `Ok((fee0, fee1, oracle_hints))` - Fees that must be repaid and oracle hints for swaps\00\00\00\00\0bflash_begin\00\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\09recipient\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\07amount0\00\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\07amount1\00\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\09initiator\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\03\e9\00\00\03\ed\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\0a\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0bOracleHints\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\efEnd a flash loan\0a\0aMust be called by the same initiator that called flash_begin().\0aVerifies repayment and clears the flash lock.\0a\0a# Returns\0a* `Ok(())` if repayment is sufficient\0a* `Err(InsufficientRepayment0/1)` if repayment is insufficient\00\00\00\00\09flash_end\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\03\e9\00\00\03\ed\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\95Returns the current pool state.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aSlot0 containing current sqrt price, tick, and lock status\00\00\00\00\00\00\05slot0\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\05Slot0\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\8eReturns whether the pool has been initialized.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0atrue if initialized, false otherwise\00\00\00\00\00\0eis_initialized\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\8eReturns the factory address that created this pool.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aAddress of the factory contract\00\00\00\00\00\07factory\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00wReturns the address of token0 in the pair.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aAddress of token0\00\00\00\00\06token0\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00wReturns the address of token1 in the pair.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aAddress of token1\00\00\00\00\06token1\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\7fReturns the pool's fee tier.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aFee in basis points (e.g., 3000 = 0.3%)\00\00\00\00\03fee\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\9eReturns the pool's tick spacing.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aTick spacing (e.g., 60 means positions must be on multiples of 60)\00\00\00\00\00\0ctick_spacing\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\01)Returns the flash executor address for this pool.\0a\0aThe flash executor is immutable and set once during pool deployment.\0aThis is the only authorized contract that can initiate flash loans on this pool.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aAddress of the FlashExecutor contract\00\00\00\00\00\00\0eflash_executor\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\99Returns the protocol fee for zero_for_one swaps from the factory.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aProtocol fee in basis points\00\00\00\00\00\00\12get_protocol_fee_0\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\99Returns the protocol fee for one_for_zero swaps from the factory.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aProtocol fee in basis points\00\00\00\00\00\00\12get_protocol_fee_1\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\d0Returns a tick bitmap word for off-chain quoters and lens contracts.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a* `word_pos` - The word position in the bitmap\0a\0a# Returns\0a256-bit word from the tick bitmap\00\00\00\0fget_tick_bitmap\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08word_pos\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\0c\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\95Returns the current active liquidity.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aTotal liquidity currently active at the current tick\00\00\00\00\00\00\09liquidity\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\82Returns the global fee growth for token0.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aFee growth in Q128.128 format\00\00\00\00\00\18fee_growth_global_0_x128\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0dFixedPoint128\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\82Returns the global fee growth for token1.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aFee growth in Q128.128 format\00\00\00\00\00\18fee_growth_global_1_x128\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0dFixedPoint128\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\98Returns the accumulated protocol fees.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a\0a# Returns\0aProtocolFees struct containing amounts for both tokens\00\00\00\0dprotocol_fees\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0cProtocolFees\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\cdReturns information about a specific tick.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a* `tick` - The tick index to query\0a\0a# Returns\0aTickInfo struct, or default (uninitialized) if tick hasn't been used\00\00\00\00\00\00\05ticks\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\04tick\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\01\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\08TickInfo\00\00\00\00\00\00\01,Returns all data needed for position fee calculations in a single call.\0a\0a# Arguments\0a* `env` - The contract environment\0a* `tick_lower` - The lower tick of the position\0a* `tick_upper` - The upper tick of the position\0a\0a# Returns\0aPositionFeeData struct containing slot0, global fee growth, and tick info\00\00\00\15get_position_fee_data\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0atick_lower\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0atick_upper\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\01\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0fPositionFeeData\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\e2Returns cumulative values inside a tick range for a given position.\0a\0aUsed to compute time-weighted averages and liquidity-weighted time within\0aa price range for liquidity mining and other analytic